ol.li:
(1) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of—


(a) any administrative expenses incurred by any government department in consequence of the provisions of that Act;


(b) any increase attributable to that Act in the sums payable out of money so provided under any other Act;

(2) the remission of the liabilities of the National Freight Corporation to the Minister of Transport in respect of—


(a) the Corporation's commencing capital debt; and

(b) loans made to the Corporation by the Minister;

(3) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of any sums required for making payments to the persons administering B.R. and N.F.C. pension schemes (as defined in that Act) being payments calculated, in relation to each scheme and for each financial year, by reference to—


(a) the proportion of the relevant pension obligations (as so defined) which has not been funded;

(b) the proportion of the pensions increases and expenses payable under or incurred in connection with the scheme which corresponds to those obligations; and

(c) the aggregate amount of the pensions, increases and expenses payable under or incurred in connection with the scheme for that year;
